For each individual who seeks to vote, an election judge, in accordance with instructions provided by the local board, shall:
locate the individual's name in the election register and locate the preprinted voting authority card and then authorize the individual to vote a regular ballot;
if the individual's name is not found on the election register, search the inactive list and if the name is found, authorize the individual to vote a regular ballot; or
if the individual's name is not on the inactive list, refer the individual for provisional ballot voting under § 9-404 of this article;
establish the identity of the voter by requesting the voter to state the month and day of the voter's birth and comparing the response to the information listed in the election register;
except if a voter's personal information has been deemed confidential by the local board, verify the address of the voter's residence; or
conduct an alternative verification as established by the State Board, if the voter's personal information has been deemed confidential by the local board;
if any changes to the voting authority card are indicated by a voter, make the appropriate changes in information on the card or other appropriate form; and
have the voter sign the voting authority card and either issue the voter a ballot or send the voter to a machine to vote.
